Source: pgrdf
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), cargo, clang, git
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/styk-tv/pgRDF

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pgrdf
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pgrdf
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: RDF, SPARQL, SHACL, and OWL reasoning for PostgreSQL
 pgRDF is a Rust-native PostgreSQL extension for RDF storage, SPARQL 1.1 query
 and update, SHACL validation, and OWL 2 RL or RDFS materialization inside
 PostgreSQL. This package builds the extension for PostgreSQL 14 through 18.
